section#elr-passwords
    .elr-container
        .elr-row
            .elr-col-full
                h1 ELR Passwords
                p.
                    Analyzes passwords for complexity. A password is considered strong if it uses a combination of
                    uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters. It should also be st least 8
                    characters.
                p ELR Passwords also ensures that passwords are not on a list of the most commonly used passwords.
    .elr-container
        .elr-row
            .elr-col-full
                form.tabular-form(role="form" action="")
                    label(for="password") *Password:
                    input.elr-valid-no-spaces.elr-password#password(type="password" name="password" required)
                    button.elr-button.elr-show-password Show Password
                .elr-col-full
                    .password-holder: p password
                    small.elr-block Be sure to store this password in a safe place
                    button.elr-button.elr-button-primary.elr-generate-password Generate Password
    .elr-container
        .elr-row
            .elr-col-full
                h2 Usage
